###Here is the fetching process where you are using the NLTK library. You will fetch the story text with urllib.

start with
>>>import nltk
>>>from urllib import request
>>>url = "http://classics.mit.edu/Homer/odyessy.mb.txt"
>>>response = request.urlopen(url)
>>>raw = response.read().decode('utf8')
>>>type(raw)
###What is a string?
<class'str'>
>>>tokens = nltk.word_tokenize(raw)
>>>type(tokens)
###What is a list?
<class 'list'>
>>>lens(tokens)
134214
